    "The main assumption underlying NSDCG is that higher results reflect closer proximity between the original and anonymized logit distributions, indicating a higher degree of similarity between the two distributions and thereby gauging the retained clinical information.",
    "The only difference from NDCG is that the discount is obtained from applying the softmax function on the transformer logits, resulting in sd (Equation 9) instead of the common logarithmic discount: log(i + 1).",
    "The discount is commonly applied to the gain represented by the relevance score rel.",
    "Consequently, the SDCG (Softmax Discounted Cumulative Gain, based on the Discounted Cumulative Gain (DCG)) is calculated as follows:",
    "As for the discount sd i, let s be the sorted (descending) logits from the original note."
